olive oil
1 onion
2 clove garlic
1 cucumber
1 packet lamb mince
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp brown sugar
20 g butter
1 bag salad leaves
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet garlic aioli
2 radish
¼ cup water
1 sachet Berbere seasoning

• Thinly slice red onion. Finely chop garlic, radish and cucumber.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. Cook onion until softened, 3 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add lamb mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Berbere spice blend, tomato paste and brown sugar. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the butter and water (for the lamb) and simmer until the sauce has thickened, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, add radish and cucumber to a medium bowl. Add a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Roughly chop roasted almonds.
• Spread garlic aioli over tortillas, then top with mixed salad leaves, Turkish-spiced lamb and cucumber salsa.
• Garnish with almonds to serve.